<div class="lb-section-row region-body"><div class="lb-region lb-region--left"><div class="block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockrelated-missions"><h2>More from UNICEF USA</h2><div class="views-element-container"><div class="view view-related-missions view-id-related_missions view-display-id-missions js-view-dom-id-5305f8b515ffeea5a092b33e85746d74fad646340b2917b44ffd55635791ab67"></div></div></div></div><div class="lb-region lb-region--right"><div class="block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockrecommended-stories-mini"><h2>Recommended Stories</h2><div class="teaser-column"><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/struggle-sustainability-sudan-transforming-lives-clean-water" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2024-02/UNI500244.jpg?itok=-iIu0Z14" width="458" height="305" alt="Children collect clean and safe water from a new water station in the small village of Gelhanty in Agig locality, Red Sea state, Sudan." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">From Struggle to Sustainability in Sudan: <strong>Transforming Lives With Clean Water</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>How UNICEF helped children and women in Gelhanty, a small and remote village in Sudan's eastern Red Sea state, gain reliable access to safe water.</p></div></a></div></article><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/surge-violence-fuels-humanitarian-crisis-haiti" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2024-02/UNI516128%20Haiti%20banner.jpg?itok=7rRTknGk" width="458" height="305" alt="Seven-year-old Lovenska of Haiti works on a drawing at a UNICEF-supported child-friendly space in Delmas 6, downtown Port-au-Prince." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Surge in Violence Fuels <strong>Humanitarian Crisis in Haiti</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Calling the situation for children "a living nightmare," UNICEF Haiti Representative Bruno Maes urges more support for the emergency response. [VIDEO]</p></div></a></div></article><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/during-ramadan-make-difference-children-need" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2024-02/UNI523442.jpg.1100w.jpg?itok=orSUfgU_" width="458" height="305" alt="Children in Kassala state, Sudan." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">During Ramadan, <strong>Make a Difference for Children in Need</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Ramadan will be difficult this year for children whose lives have been turned upside-down by conflict in Gaza, Sudan and Yemen. [VIDEO]</p></div></a></div></article></div></div></div></div> </section>
